          "position": [35.52, -84.36],
          "text": "## Chota \n In 1776, Indigenous representatives from northern Nations met in the Cherokee town of Chota, which had grown powerful as a “terminus” of Southern trading routes. Sometimes referred to as the “Grand Talk,” these representatives appealed to the Cherokee to form a united front against settler-colonial incursions (Kane, 2018; 19, 43-45)."
